==English==
===Pronunciation===
s&-'mi-l&-"tüd, -"tyüd
===Etymology===
Middle English, from Middle French, resemblance, likeness, from Latin similitudo, from similis
===Noun===
'''similitude'''
# [[similarity]] or [[resemblance]] to something else
# someone or something that closely [[resemble]]s another; a [[duplicate]] or [[twin]]

